    <section>
      <h4>About</h4>
      <p>ColorGeek is a web application for creating and sharing color palettes.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Guests have to register for being able to create, share and like palettes</li>
        <li>User can create private palettes, share best palettes with other users.</li>
        <li>User can like palettes, and palettes with the biggest number of likes are available on Popular page.</li>
        <li>It's possible to edit and save private palettes.</li>
        <li>User can make a copy of any public palette to user's palettes.</li>
        <li>On click on a color cell selected color's value is copying to clipboard.</li>
        <li>It's possible to choose color mode: hex(default) or rgb</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h4>Technologies</h4>
      <p>Main technologies used for ColorGeek development are:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Vue.js 2 - progressive JavaScript framework</li>
        <li>Vue-router for app routing</li>
        <li>Vuex for state management</li>
        <li>Vue-cli for scaffolding project</li>
        <li>Firebase for authentification and realtime database</li>
        <li>And other libraries and tools: Clipboard.js, Webpack, Babel, ESLint, etc.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Source code of the application: <a href="https://github.com/fremdev/colorgeek" target="_blank">https://github.com/fremdev/colorgeek</a></p>
    </section>
